stors should start preparing for the end of the credit cycle according to tcw group inc’s tad rivelle“the creditfuelled expansion inevitably comes to a bad end” rivelle chief investment officer for fixed income at tcw said in a note sent to investors tuesday “we’ve lived this story before”other fixedincome investors such as bill gross and jeffrey gundlach have warned that central bank policies are fueling asset bubbles which will eventually burst triggering financial market turmoil corporate leverage in america soared to new heights this month as sales of company bonds passed  trillion for the fifth consecutive year total company debt is at a record  times collective earnings as of june according to a sept  estimate from morgan stanley the ratio fell to  in  when the us economy started recovering from the great recessionrivelle whose firm oversees  billion blames central bankers for fueling asset bubbles which are bound to collapse as leverage goes up faster than income available to service debt“our counsel remains as it has been avoid those assets that will be broken in the coming deleveraging while keeping a ‘steady as she goes’ attitude towards the future purchase of those assets that will merely bend when the flood come” rivelle wroterivelle’s  billion metropolitan west total return bond fund has gained an average  percent over the past five years outperforming  percent of its bloomberg peers the fund is up  percent this year outperforming only  percent of peers before its here its on the bloomberg terminal learn more most read jeff bezos briefly tops bill gates as the worlds richest person rollsroyce unveils its grandest car yet the phantom viii here come the tesla model s  and a few surprises libor funeral set for  as fca abandons scandaltarred rate amazon reminds market that dominating ecommerce has a price tcwcom  trading secrets here be dragons aboutour firmour partnersour peopleour historycareerscontact usclient solutionsus institutional investorsconsultan